Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.61,0:01:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,To Icy Tail's first solo performance!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.55,0:01:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheers!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.63,0:01:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.80,0:01:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomo here is paying for everything, so let's go nuts!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.51,0:02:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.64,0:02:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Could we get ten orders each of \Nbeef tongue, grilled beef, sirloin steak, beef tripe and...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.31,0:02:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, no more!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.90,0:02:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, solo gigs are the best, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.60,0:02:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Right? Everyone is there just for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.48,0:02:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And that many people, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.03,0:02:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The dressing room was so spacious.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.86,0:02:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually there's barely any room for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.53,0:02:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? That's supposed to be the best part?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.35,0:02:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it, Tomoya-senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.49,0:02:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Our new game's promotion is going great!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.21,0:02:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure is, and it's all thanks to your hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.25,0:02:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I did finish that key visual at ten this morning, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.88,0:02:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to that, we barely got the merch done in time...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.48,0:02:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.89,0:02:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been working yourself to death for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.73,0:02:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's our job as fellow circle members to back you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.69,0:02:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Megumi-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.32,0:02:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is that even though everyone's giving it their all,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.31,0:03:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,there is still one member who hasn't contributed anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.39,0:03:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Katou...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.45,0:03:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me guess, you're talking about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.96,0:03:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't exactly trying to be subtle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.83,0:03:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Me-Megumi-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.28,0:03:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not a fan of taking on work \Nthat anyone else could do, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.13,0:03:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that as a member of the circle, \Ntrying to help out where you can is a given.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.35,0:03:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish you'd consider how much \Ncareful effort I put in to prepare for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.31,0:03:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You do understand how much it's worth, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.57,0:03:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Michiru.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.39,0:03:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do these two hate each other so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.91,0:03:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Why would I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.62,0:03:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're asking Micchi, you must truly be lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.70,0:03:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,She's the most clueless person in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.62,0:03:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why she could never join in on the Holy Girlfriend War.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.54,0:03:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, what is this war I'm just getting to hear about?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.88,0:04:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, Katou-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.69,0:04:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The advertisement I put out on Twitter has hit over five thousand retweets.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.10,0:04:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means, I've already spread the news of our work \Nto over ten times the size of this concert's audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.23,0:04:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty sure that's just advertising, \Nwhich doesn't help in making the game at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.28,0:04:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Selling merch at a concert isn't getting the game done any faster either, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.41,0:04:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahh! It's on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.54,0:04:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you not to put it all there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.46,0:04:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Katou-san has changed, hasn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.90,0:04:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Heh? What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.07,0:04:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Just thinking how we were always in the spotlight in the TV series,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.76,0:04:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so now it's hard to adjust to being side characters in the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.30,0:04:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only fair. We're not part of the circle anymore, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.52,0:04:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The probably cast us as bottom-of-the-barrel actresses.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.02,0:04:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for coming here tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.27,0:05:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Eriri, Kasumigaoka-senpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.15,0:05:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we should be thanking you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.24,0:05:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad you invited us, Megumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.07,0:05:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So how are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.41,0:05:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.45,0:05:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, work has been hell, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.80,0:05:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Fields Chronicle is a huge project, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.42,0:05:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,With the scenario written by Kasumigaoka Utaha, \NI'll have a hard time believing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.34,0:05:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I see we are getting along as well as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.17,0:05:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You two really are close, as usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.05,0:05:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What gave you that idea? All we ever do is argue.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.52,0:05:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys are getting closer too, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.02,0:05:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, since when were you able\N to argue with Hashima like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.27,0:05:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.77,0:05:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you know, you have to sterilize any \Nforeign objects that make it into your circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.41,0:05:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you in luck, then? That the all-important \NSawamura-san here was so kind and easy to tame.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.37,0:05:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What are you implying?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.86,0:05:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Rinri-kun,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.46,0:06:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,come over here for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.75,0:06:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Utaha-senpai...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.96,0:06:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We haven't seen each other in so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.01,0:06:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's have a good, long talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.34,0:06:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,S-Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.22,0:06:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.32,0:06:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to worry about what happened back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.92,0:06:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, it was my first time, but I don't regret doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.56,0:06:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, please! That's enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.94,0:06:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! I remember!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.82,0:06:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened, Eriri?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.61,0:06:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Get this, Megumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.16,0:06:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Please! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.16,0:06:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,This woman... This wench!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.42,0:06:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Katou... uh... that was just...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.58,0:06:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You really shouldn't tease Eriri so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.43,0:06:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you two supposed to be\N getting along and working together?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.64,0:07:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? So you think this is between just me and Eriri?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.52,0:07:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if that's what you're talking about,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.59,0:07:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,then we still have plenty to discuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.49,0:07:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,How about you go sit at another table, Aki-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.75,0:07:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,How have you been, Rinri-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.21,0:07:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Great. Until just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.79,0:07:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.67,0:07:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how much you regret it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.34,0:07:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that you've hurt me so much,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.34,0:07:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and that you were my first man won't ever change.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.39,0:07:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't regret anything until you started talking!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.68,0:07:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You're so clingy!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.56,0:07:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A college student still drooling \Nover a high schooler? Disgusting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.56,0:07:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you? Still stuck on that \Nchildhood friend you've betrayed twice?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.82,0:07:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,How's that for sad?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.79,0:07:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm perfectly fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.07,0:07:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, he forgave me both times.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.40,0:07:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That just means your relationship \Nwas reset back to nothing, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.70,0:07:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you two ever grow up?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.44,0:08:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So how is it going?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.38,0:08:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Blessing Software's new game?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.92,0:08:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave it to me. Just watch, you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.76,0:08:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, I'll make it with my own two hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.38,0:08:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,A gal-game that everyone will be thrilled to play!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.39,0:08:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This is only your second game, and you went and \Nwrote the scenarios for all five heroines all by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.52,0:08:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you determined?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.73,0:08:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You were just a moe-loving pig until last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.94,0:08:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't think that's changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.43,0:08:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, well, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.78,0:08:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomoya-senpai might be a disgusting moe-lover,\Nbut his scenario here is really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.53,0:08:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I get so excited every time he finishes a new scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.41,0:08:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm like, what poses should I use here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.50,0:08:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What expressions should I use in this scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.92,0:08:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, there are still a few issues.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.38,0:08:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Like the blonde, twin-tailed heroine,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.80,0:08:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,or the similarly-clichéd heroine with long, black hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.30,0:08:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they really even necessary?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.18,0:09:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Though to make up for that, there's the cute and courageous underclassmen heroine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.06,0:09:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So overall, the scenario is still legendary.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.23,0:09:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure you're talking about just the scenario here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.40,0:09:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides the scenario, with Michiru-senpai's BGM, Megumi-san's direction, and my art,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.82,0:09:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it will turn out to be perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.62,0:09:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So, even if you two are working \Non a big project with a huge budget,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.04,0:09:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,if it gets delayed and turns out to be trash, \Nit will just end up in the garbage bin.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.08,0:09:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't come crying to us if that happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.96,0:09:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the one crying here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.96,0:09:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Right back at you, Hashima Izumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.55,0:09:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I admire that reckless confidence of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.34,0:09:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, can you promise me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.26,0:09:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That you'll make a legendary game that can compete with ours?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.18,0:09:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a given.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.98,0:09:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When it comes down to it, our teamwork is second to none.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.86,0:09:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't underestimate us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.09,0:10:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.34,0:10:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing, Kousaka-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.59,0:10:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Worming your way into a get-together like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.59,0:10:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You're insane. Being rude has its limits, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.59,0:10:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Object all you want. I'm just here \Nto give feedback as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.18,0:10:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you to sent it over at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.02,0:10:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what happens when you send it during the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.56,0:10:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We forced ourselves to finish things early because we had plans later!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.61,0:10:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately for you, those plans are canceled.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.90,0:10:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a private discussion, Tomoya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.74,0:10:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.95,0:10:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.99,0:10:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This has to look like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.08,0:10:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.20,0:10:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That won't look any good on screen!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.08,0:10:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you retarded, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.58,0:10:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,How is this armor supposed to work?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.75,0:10:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If we do things your way, \Nthe design would be way too plain!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.09,0:10:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about the overall balance!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.55,0:10:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This one piece is floating!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.92,0:11:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Designing this is my job, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.05,0:11:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So just shut up and let me draw it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.89,0:11:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Not if you're going to give me this bullshit!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.47,0:11:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Rethink this whole thing from the top and try again!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.97,0:11:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.02,0:11:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Iori... uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.02,0:11:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we are in Akihabara after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.86,0:11:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I've told Akane-san many times not to discuss work in public like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.69,0:11:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hardly a private meeting anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.78,0:11:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,U-Uh, please don't take pictures or share this anywhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.99,0:11:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh, this has no impact at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.83,0:11:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell is this scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.62,0:11:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You just can't appreciate the subtlety!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.83,0:11:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Please just stop arguing and eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.42,0:11:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What aren't you understanding?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.04,0:11:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This scene where Philene dies\N is supposed to be the climax of the first half!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.63,0:11:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And the spoilers were out\N before the climax even existed...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.72,0:11:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the one who doesn't get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.01,0:11:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Describing this scene slowly and quietly\N can have an even greater impact!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.14,0:11:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You want me to throw in some boring, run-of-the-mill crying scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.39,0:11:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Players have seen enough of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.81,0:11:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Then give it more of an edge!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.60,0:11:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Make it run through the players' hearts like a blade!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.48,0:12:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can't handle that, all that's left is this pretentious hot air!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.65,0:12:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.36,0:12:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.78,0:12:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're bothering the other customers...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.91,0:12:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry, we've caused you {\i1}so{\i0} much trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.41,0:12:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take care of all their bills.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.54,0:12:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You get what I'm saying, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.17,0:12:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Eat all you want, and forget everything you heard here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.67,0:12:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Beef tongue, grilled beef, sirloin steak, beef tripe,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.05,0:12:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take everything you've got!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.94,0:12:36.19,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnBrush Stroke\fs72\be2\pos(964.133,100.8)\frz359.9\c&H1E1E21&}Out of meat for the day
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.23,0:12:43.57,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnAvantGarde Bk BT Eclipse\be1\fs72\fade(1000,1000)\i1\pos(604.8,119.2)}How to Raise a Boring Girlfriend. Fine
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.96,0:13:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, I don't have the appetite.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.21,0:13:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,When did you go to sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.13,0:13:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I was planning to stay awake until everyone got here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.26,0:13:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,How are things progressing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.89,0:13:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Who was it that, back in July, \Nsaid he could take it easy over summer break
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.02,0:13:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,because only the main heroine's route was left?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.31,0:14:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that was only a {\i1}little{\i0} while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.02,0:14:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And how much time is left before summer break ends?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.07,0:14:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a {\i1}little{\i0} while...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.36,0:14:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Izumi-chan might be stuck without\N work waiting on the scenario soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.99,0:14:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.50,0:14:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in a slump. What am I supposed to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.91,0:14:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Which part are you on now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.67,0:14:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Meguri 15.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.05,0:14:27.76,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs72\be1\move(890,733,380,733)\c&H1D1D1D&}After the player makes the final choice to select Meguri as heroine
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.05,0:14:27.76,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs72\be1\move(2032,733,1522,733)\c&H1D1D1D&}(start of Meguri route)
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.59,0:14:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'm not too familiar with this stuff,\N but even I can tell that this is important.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.76,0:14:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.63,0:14:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The event that kicks off Meguri's route.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.10,0:14:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The big climax at the turning point of the story!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.89,0:14:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This part has to be perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.77,0:14:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.06,0:14:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to write the greatest scene in the game!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.86,0:14:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what's the plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.28,0:14:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Katou.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.82,0:14:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,How am I supposed to get around my writer's block?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.16,0:14:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You're asking me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.49,0:14:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What else can I do? I'm stuck! Help me out!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.62,0:15:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And this feeling that you're not really \Nrelying on me, is just in my head, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.71,0:15:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.21,0:15:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,How about trying to learn from other people's work?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.01,0:15:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. We shouldn't underestimate \Nthe work of our predecessors, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.97,0:15:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Or maybe you could just keep writing \None attempt after the other for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.14,0:15:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.52,0:15:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Hundred kilobytes of trash \Nis still better than a zero kilobyte masterpiece.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.52,0:15:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Or maybe you could just \Nstop thinking about it and get some rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.19,0:15:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely! It's very much possible that a group \Nof little elves will finish my work while I'm asleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.78,0:15:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't really have the time \Nto try out that option right now, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.12,0:15:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Katou. What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.66,0:15:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, instead of asking me, \Nwhy don't you try asking an expert?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.00,0:15:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,300)}You mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.30,0:15:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Hasn't she been though the same thing\N that you're going through right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.22,0:15:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe Kasumigaoka-senpai could help—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.56,0:16:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But... if I asked Utaha-senpai for advice...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.81,0:16:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Would it be okay with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.31,0:16:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Why wouldn't it be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.73,0:16:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that time at the barbecue place...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.57,0:16:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Kasumigaoka-senpai may not be in our circle anymore, but if it's for our game, I think I could tolerate her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.45,0:16:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.99,0:16:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait one minute, Katou!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.20,0:16:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Your words and expression don't line up at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.54,0:16:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.59,0:16:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Hyoudou-san and Izumi-chan should be here soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.76,0:16:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you at least wash your face?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.51,0:16:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.82,0:16:54.82,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs65\be1 \c&H565559&\pos(434.533,338.933)}Event Number: Meguri 15
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.91,0:17:06.42,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnHelvetica Neue\fs50\fscx88\c&H171719&\frx2\be1\fry2\pos(949.866,747.2)\frz17.05}I was running some errands and ended up near your place. You home?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.09,0:17:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,'Sup.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.13,0:17:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too bad Kasumi-sensei was out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.06,0:17:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you there for today?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.35,0:17:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,She sent over a revised scenario this morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.35,0:17:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's still no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.35,0:17:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You should have asked her before driving over.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.98,0:17:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to hear that from the guy who was \Nstanding outside her apartment like a stalker.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.40,0:17:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll have to be bolder than that\N if you want to get her back, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.07,0:17:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Your position as head of your circle aside, as a man—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.99,0:17:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That is {\i1}not{\i} why I was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.50,0:17:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to ask for some help with my scenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.46,0:17:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, I don't want to hear that from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.34,0:17:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I{\i} was the one who discovered Kashiwagi Eri and Kasumi Utako.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.76,0:17:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They were well known in the doujin and novel worlds\N long before you even noticed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.76,0:18:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But still, making a game with their talents \Ncombined was {\i1}my{\i} idea which {\i1}you{\i0} stole.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.98,0:18:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you {\i1}have{\i0} to be so mean? And to your savior, at that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.19,0:18:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Since when did you—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.90,0:18:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Enaka-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.65,0:18:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Even after I drove you all the way to Nasu Kougen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.99,0:18:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In the middle of the night, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.66,0:18:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.33,0:18:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I missed four deadlines thanks to that, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.96,0:18:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You have no idea how much bullshit I got from my editor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.42,0:18:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.71,0:18:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute, Kousaka-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.21,0:18:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Did seeing Eriri's art back then \Nmade you want to work with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.30,0:18:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.84,0:18:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess that makes me your unlucky charm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.23,0:18:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me out! Stop the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.52,0:18:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Good idea. I'm tired of all this driving. Let's grab a bite.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.65,0:18:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what I meant!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.82,0:19:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... Kousaka-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.28,0:19:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up, I'm trying to focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.83,0:19:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, are you actually reading it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.17,0:19:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, I haven't missed a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.79,0:19:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's inhuman.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.76,0:19:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! You're definitely not laughing \Nout of appreciation for my writing, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.85,0:19:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What the heck? It's so creepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.23,0:19:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially this blonde haired heroine who cries after a kiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.19,0:19:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I reading? What kinda crazy pure maiden is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.73,0:19:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Even in 2D, a girl this extreme is rare.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.24,0:19:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to explain every detail!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.95,0:19:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,M-My sides!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.33,0:19:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Just stop...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.87,0:19:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, no more...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.95,0:19:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This long, black haired heroine's \Nmood swings are pretty insane too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.91,0:19:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Normally she's so sadistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.17,0:19:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Why the heck does she become a shy little girl in bed?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.80,0:20:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Just so you know, they're just \Nsleeping in the same bed, nothing more!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.51,0:20:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what's with this
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.93,0:20:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,"E-Even though I'm usually like that, this is actually my first time..."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.51,0:20:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell is that supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.47,0:20:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't act it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.24,0:20:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the main heroine's scenario...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.24,0:20:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only partially finished, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.62,0:20:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,H-How is it? I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.00,0:20:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to hear your honest opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.59,0:20:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You progressed a lot while writing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.38,0:20:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a far cry from what you wrote for the sub-heroines.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.93,0:20:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Earlier it was a disgusting mess of a script,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.98,0:20:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but it becomes a lot more refined in the main heroine's route.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.10,0:20:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I never would have expected for you to change so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.06,0:20:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Amateurs who stumble onto the right path are scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.19,0:21:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad to hear it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.82,0:21:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is, I wasn't sure if I was headed in the right direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.15,0:21:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I could tell things were different and thought \NI was in a slump, but I had actually improved!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.41,0:21:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I was actually making progress!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.87,0:21:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much. \NI feel like I've regained my confidence thanks to—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.38,0:21:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.13,0:21:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Moron!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.13,0:21:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The one thing you got right was doubting yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.93,0:21:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a good thing you slumped! It's good that you stopped!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.68,0:21:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You were this close to turning everything into a pile of trash!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.77,0:21:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.39,0:21:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Your script is getting so polished it's bland.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.77,0:21:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this inoffensive garbage?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.65,0:21:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you getting shy? That's not like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.15,0:21:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But just now, weren't you saying that this was a far cry from all the previous routes?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.99,0:21:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How the hell is this heap of dense shit \Nsupposed to compete with a polished turd?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.50,0:22:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In Cherry Blessing, weren't you the one \Nwho wrote that painfully positive route?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.75,0:22:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way Kasumi-sensei could write something so corny.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.67,0:22:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The first half of your scenario here is basically the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.59,0:22:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's... well...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.35,0:22:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Even I couldn't have ever written something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.10,0:22:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That's your weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.52,0:22:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Kousaka-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.02,0:22:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Your strength is in writing these dumb otaku fantasies!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.73,0:22:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's exciting. It's embarrassing. \NIt makes you want to look away!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.24,0:22:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hot garbage that you end up craving for!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.70,0:22:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're complimenting me, \Ncould you not call my work garbage?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.99,0:22:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The disgusting otaku of the world will gladly eat it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.16,0:22:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to get better, focus on those fantasies!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.66,0:22:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Let your inane desires flow!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.08,0:22:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Flirt with your overly-cunning heroine like crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.00,0:22:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.88,0:22:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, it's like masturbation!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.67,0:22:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like masturbation, young man!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.01,0:22:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Masturbation that makes you feel amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.51,0:22:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Masturbation that everyone wants to see!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.22,0:22:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Take something as incredibly embarrassing \Nas masturbation, and show it off!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.48,0:23:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.74,0:23:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what are you gonna do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.57,0:23:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanna stop by Kasumi-sensei's place with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.82,0:23:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna head home.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.70,0:23:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, then. I'll see you later, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.87,0:23:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Kousaka-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.42,0:23:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,For today... uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.42,0:23:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,When you've finished the game, save me a copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.67,0:23:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll pick it up at Winter Comiket.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.22,0:23:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.19,0:23:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold up! Don't drive! Get a taxi!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.32,0:23:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's how it is, Katou!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.28,0:23:52.78,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs46\fax0.5\be3\pos(1005.429,415.714)\frz4.808\c&HECECEC&\1a&H1C&}Megumi
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.74,0:23:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... I'm not really sure what you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.78,0:23:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason behind my slump.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.57,0:23:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, I need to focus on my disgusting fantasies!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.83,0:23:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to masturbate more!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.54,0:24:00.54,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs46\fax0.5\be3\pos(1005.429,415.714)\frz4.808\c&HF69863&\1a&H1C&}Megumi
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.42,0:24:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, that came out wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.25,0:24:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What I wanted to say was that I need to \Nfocus on writing self-satisfying fantasies.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.92,0:24:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you have to write something even {\i1}more{\i} disgusting?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.18,0:24:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I could stand that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.60,0:24:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe girls wouldn't be able to stand it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.93,0:24:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But guys like me will lap it up! It makes our heart flutter!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.85,0:24:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So basically, isn't this the worst possible situation for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.23,0:24:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, before starting Meguri 15,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.07,0:24:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I rewrote Meguri 01 through Meguri 14.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.82,0:24:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Aki-kun, what's today's date again?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.45,0:24:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... August 31st.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.71,0:24:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And when does our summer break end?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.00,0:24:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,August 31st.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.21,0:24:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Mind if I say something else?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.55,0:24:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't! I don't care about any homework or tests!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.72,0:24:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This year, I decided to put everything I can into this game!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.22,0:24:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We're third years, we'll have college entrance exams soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.06,0:25:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'll send over the updated Meguri scenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.06,0:25:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a video call once you've read it \Nso we can talk it over while going through.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.81,0:25:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, look, Aki-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.19,0:25:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what time it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.40,0:25:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care what time it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.15,0:25:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Later!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.66,0:25:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I've finished reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.62,0:25:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You actually called me back today itself...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.91,0:25:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.50,0:25:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No! Thank you so much! Katou-sama! Megumi-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.08,0:25:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just start going over everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.34,0:25:32.71,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs48\be1\c&H565559&\pos(417.39,346.933)}Event Number: Meguri 04
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.00,0:25:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, this scene is just no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.71,0:25:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The protagonist's actions, dialogue, attitude, \Nand basically everything about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.64,0:25:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.05,0:25:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, if a guy is this self-absorbed, \Nno girl would be able to stand him.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.52,0:25:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a man's fantasy!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.85,0:25:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In a story like this, that attitude \Nawakens the girl's womanly instincts!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.44,0:25:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,She'll think, "Well, I guess I'll play along," and it'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.78,0:25:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In reality, she'd think, "Well, I guess we're breaking up,"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.16,0:25:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and just end things right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.78,0:26:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not talking about the real world!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.53,0:26:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We're talking about men's fantasies!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.83,0:26:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But still, you can't go {\i1}that{\i} far.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.37,0:26:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,R-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.75,0:26:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to be more considerate of the heroine.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.34,0:26:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if it's just once in a while, treat her nicely, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.05,0:26:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So how should I fix this?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.01,0:26:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that something {\i1}you{\i0} should come up with?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.68,0:26:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You're being awfully strict.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.10,0:26:28.98,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs50\be1\c&H565559&\pos(381.961,366.362)}Event Number: Meguri 14
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.81,0:26:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.98,0:26:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.15,0:26:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, isn't this event right before the one \Nthat starts the heroine's route?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.24,0:26:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.74,0:26:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, isn't this the event where Meguri begins to fall for the protagonist?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.20,0:26:44.83,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs60\c&H3E3D40&\pos(629.123,684.533)\1a&H15&}Meguri and the protagonist make up
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.83,0:26:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is such an ordinary event the one that raises her flag?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.58,0:26:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's as if you've been in her route the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.34,0:26:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that—
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.22,0:27:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, that's why it's terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.76,0:27:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You should... um... change it a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.52,0:27:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No. There's no way I'm changing this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.65,0:27:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Of all the scenes I've written, this one is my favorite.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.57,0:27:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I love this scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.32,0:27:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why are you asking for my input?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.03,0:27:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You can just write it yourself, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.33,0:27:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Katou...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.08,0:27:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheer up, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.50,0:27:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like I'm mad at you or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.67,0:27:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, then can we take a look at Meguri 15 now?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.30,0:27:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Just the plot.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.26,0:27:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I really want to know how you feel about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.34,0:27:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You can just write it however you want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.98,0:27:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you before, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.39,0:27:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This has to be the best scene in the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.39,0:27:54.23,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs65\be1 \c&H565559&\pos(434.533,338.933)}Event Number: Meguri 15
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.23,0:27:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I really need you for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.74,0:28:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You're so self-absorbed and pushy, Aki-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.57,0:28:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.91,0:28:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... I think I'd change at least a part of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.37,0:28:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Which part?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.58,0:28:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, when something sad happens, and the protagonist is crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.42,0:28:18.42,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs69\be1\c&H504F55&\pos(1004.2,366.4)}He thought he had lost everything, but then she returned back to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.42,0:28:18.42,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs69\be1\c&H504F55&\pos(513.296,627.924)}The protagonist begins to cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.42,0:28:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, having the protagonist cry was not a good idea after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.18,0:28:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Having something like that raise a flag isn't right, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.76,0:28:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.52,0:28:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem here is with the heroine.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.60,0:28:38.36,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs65\be1\c&H504F55&\pos(551.6,378.8)}"Would it be okay for me to cry?"
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.60,0:28:38.36,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs65\be1\c&H504F55&\pos(530.267,654.4)}Meguri embraces the protagonist.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.10,0:28:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,She shouldn't hug him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.69,0:28:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.15,0:28:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.36,0:28:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't it mean that Meguri's flag wasn't raised?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.65,0:28:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't. Not in the slightest.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.95,0:28:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Her flag was raised long before this part.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.49,0:28:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So here, she should let the protagonist cry his heart out.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.58,0:28:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think the players would understand that?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.75,0:29:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If they don't understand that much, \Nthey'll never be able to enter the Meguri route.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.59,0:29:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.68,0:29:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.47,0:29:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's how you think, I'll touch it up a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.47,0:29:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep up the good work, Tomoya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.43,0:29:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Katou, did you just...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.02,0:29:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.69,0:29:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,After this scene, they start calling \Neach other by their first names, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.77,0:29:24.53,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs60\be1\c&H504F55&\pos(991.6,639.467)}After that, Meguri and the protagonist start calling each other by their first names.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.73,0:29:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah, in the game, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.95,0:29:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's fine, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.57,0:29:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. I guess it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.74,0:29:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.04,0:29:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.46,0:29:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll get a little more work done before going to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.79,0:29:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye, Megumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.25,0:29:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.59,0:29:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye, Tomoya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.22,0:29:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.47,0:29:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey... Megumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.89,0:29:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Tomoya-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.89,0:29:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You can end the call now.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.60,0:30:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to sleep anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.77,0:30:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything wrong with me watching?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.65,0:30:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Not really...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.40,0:30:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So don't worry about it. Just pretend I'm not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.82,0:30:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How am I supposed to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.67,0:30:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.01,0:30:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,G-Good morning, Megumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.73,0:30:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Tomoya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.48,0:30:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What a relief...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.23,0:30:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What'd you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.40,0:30:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought this might end up like that\Ntime I called out to you back in April,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.03,0:30:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and you just started laughing all of a sudden.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.99,0:30:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I absolutely 100% don't remember doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.95,0:30:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You did! You definitely did!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.04,0:30:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw my new glasses, and were all "ugh."
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.71,0:31:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If you keep this up, \NI'm going back to calling you "Aki-kun."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.04,0:31:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,My apologies!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.63,0:31:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Please forgive me, Megumi-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.05,0:31:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.64,0:31:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So what time did you end up getting to sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.89,0:31:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is, I basically didn't—
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.60,0:31:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomoya-senpai—
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.14,0:31:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you still write without getting any sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.65,0:31:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Are those two...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.52,0:31:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Megumi, Tomoya. Morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.03,0:31:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.20,0:31:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Eriri.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.95,0:31:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if you just {\i1}have{\i0} to be that dense to be a genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.71,0:31:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I finally finished it, Meguri 15.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.79,0:31:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You couldn't write anything for the entire month,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.09,0:31:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but once you got started, it only took one night, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.30,0:31:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, this is the best thing I've written.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.97,0:31:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's my masterpiece, with both of our hearts in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.09,0:31:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead, have a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.39,0:31:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Sorry for the wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.80,0:31:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's your iced coffee. Please enjoy!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.94,0:32:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This might take a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.43,0:32:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to sit here and watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.65,0:32:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it. Just try not to get \Ndistracted and concentrate on reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.21,0:32:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,How was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.75,0:32:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It was so embarrassing I wanted to stop reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.50,0:32:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.59,0:32:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That wasn't a compliment.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.84,0:32:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If a girl feels embarrassed reading it,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.20,0:32:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure the guys will get all excited by it!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.63,0:32:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Katou.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.43,0:32:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I said, I wasn't complimenting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.31,0:32:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And you shouldn't be calling me "Katou."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.81,0:32:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Sorry, Megumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.44,0:32:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So? What comes next?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.82,0:32:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.07,0:32:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The protagonist and Meguri have finally gotten together...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.99,0:32:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Meguri going to lose her memory?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.12,0:32:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Or maybe the protagonist will die?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.99,0:33:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you forget the entire idea behind this game?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.04,0:33:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.83,0:33:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I could, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.96,0:33:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Our first priority is showing off how amazing the heroine is.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.92,0:33:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So naturally, after this...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.76,0:33:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going to flirt like crazy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.59,0:33:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I figured...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.55,0:33:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So t-tonight...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.39,0:33:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we going to do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.43,0:33:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Well... If you're tired, we don't have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.89,0:33:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.65,0:33:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.23,0:33:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's for the game, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.03,0:33:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.32,0:33:34.32,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs65\be2\c&H1D1819&\pos(392.437,334.743)}Event Number: Meguri 16
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.86,0:33:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, is this what you wrote up based on our meeting last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.07,0:33:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.08,0:33:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The first all-out flirting event between the \Nprotagonist and Meguri after they start dating.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.75,0:33:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that mean you're writing a second, or even a third?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.04,0:33:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll think about that after this is finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.21,0:33:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, I wanted you to take a look at this part here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.05,0:34:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,"Meguri trembled slightly. But after a short while, \NI found her small hand tightly grasping my own."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.85,0:34:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,"Lots of people were waiting at the train station alongside us."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.44,0:34:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,"Hidden amongst that crowd was a newly-formed couple."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.11,0:34:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,"Enjoying the innocent thrill of performing this small act of affection in public."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.91,0:34:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. After reading that \Nincredibly embarrassing excerpt out loud,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.71,0:34:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,what is it that you want from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.83,0:34:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,W-What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.38,0:34:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The heroine's reaction here...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.00,0:34:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's incredibly moe, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.38,0:34:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And what would I know about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.67,0:34:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that maybe you could help me express the heroine's feelings here.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.84,0:34:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There are plenty of ways she could react to this, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.64,0:34:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And you want me to decide?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.52,0:34:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I figured that reading it out at an actual train\N station would help set the mood a bit better.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.69,0:34:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,How would I know how she'd feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.99,0:35:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine if it's not perfect, could you still—
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.20,0:35:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,How could I know if I've never experienced it?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.38,0:35:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is such an old-school event.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.38,0:35:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the perfect event for otaku guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.88,0:35:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you want to know whether this \Nis embarrassing or not, it absolutely is.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.64,0:35:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.22,0:35:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But couldn't this be made into an \Neven more of a special moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.68,0:35:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,How is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.31,0:35:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, I think... maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.57,0:35:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,With a more intimate grip?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.82,0:35:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And what exactly would that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.32,0:35:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.99,0:35:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.16,0:35:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,She's the main heroine after all,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.45,0:35:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to go at least this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.95,0:35:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, isn't this a bit {\i1}too{\i} intimate?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.12,0:35:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You've had more intimate contact \Nwith a certain other person, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.67,0:35:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you {\i1}have{\i0} to bring that up right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.84,0:36:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You've even kissed, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.43,0:36:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,1000)}Come on, how am I supposed to use this in the script?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.27,0:36:11.02,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs65\be1\c&H424145&\pos(663.333,321.333)}Event Number: Meguri 20
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.35,0:36:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not sure where to go next?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.02,0:36:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.14,0:36:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,For Meguri 20, I have two ideas on how to handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.52,0:36:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The first?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.90,0:36:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,To write a climax for the scenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.49,0:36:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Like some sort of large event?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.11,0:36:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.12,0:36:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, Meguri could lose her memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.37,0:36:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Or maybe the protagonist could die.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.95,0:36:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.12,0:36:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, we've showed off the heroine's appeal a lot by now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.25,0:36:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought maybe we should change things up a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.54,0:36:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't decided exactly what to do yet, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.30,0:36:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright. What's your other idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.55,0:36:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, without really changing anything, \Nwe could just keep up the lovey-dovey events.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.77,0:36:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Until the end?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.31,0:36:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.65,0:37:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure if players would like it \Nif we go with that kind of half-hearted ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.82,0:37:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The story would be a bit lacking in variety...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.66,0:37:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think it would be lacking at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.37,0:37:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting into a relationship with the \Nperson you love takes a lot of courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.37,0:37:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't really think calling that half-hearted is fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.59,0:37:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't think we need any sort of big climax?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.09,0:37:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.05,0:37:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.30,0:37:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.39,0:37:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, then let's go with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.10,0:37:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No last-minute serious developments.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.81,0:37:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll add even more lovey-dovey dates, \Nkissing, and that kind of stuff instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.73,0:37:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.31,0:37:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.85,0:37:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That takes care of our next scouting trip location.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.94,0:37:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Saturday, September 23rd, at one o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.90,0:37:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,At Ikebukuro.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.24,0:37:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a walk around town and try to come up with material.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.74,0:37:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll send the details over to you later. See ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.29,0:37:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.33,0:37:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,About going around town next Saturday...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.67,0:37:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have other plans?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.08,0:38:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.80,0:38:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have anything else planned...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.30,0:38:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know what day that is, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.39,0:38:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Your birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.89,0:38:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just going out to gather material, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.93,0:38:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.73,0:38:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we not?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.81,0:38:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Which would you rather it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.02,0:38:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.78,0:38:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,A-Alright then...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.57,0:38:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If I said it wasn't just for \Ngathering material, would you still come?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.16,0:38:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.37,0:38:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go no matter what the reason is.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.62,0:38:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll look forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.54,0:38:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.08,0:38:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.88,0:38:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how it'll go Tomoya-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.13,0:38:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't blame me for whatever happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.55,0:38:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you—
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.81,0:39:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Megumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.56,0:39:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.52,0:39:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's kind of hard to explain right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.28,0:39:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but someone's life is in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.20,0:39:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll call you later and tell you all about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.66,0:39:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll definitely call and explain everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.61,0:40:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomoya!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.99,0:40:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Eriri, Utaha-senpai...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.21,0:40:44.21,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnBPreplay\fs64\be1\c&H483618&\move(828,777,504,777)}Patient's Name                      {\fnLauren C. Brown\fs82\b1\be1\c&H65513C&}Akane Kousaka
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.39,0:40:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Your business card?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.26,0:40:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We exchanged cards when we \Nran into each other the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.60,0:41:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently she collapsed in front of a convenience store,\N and didn't have any ID on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.52,0:41:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Just my business card in her pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.82,0:41:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,She never carried any cards or a license or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.49,0:41:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing in her bag was always cash.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.24,0:41:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What did the doctor say?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.54,0:41:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,She had a stroke.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.54,0:41:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When the ambulance arrived, she couldn't even talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.92,0:41:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently that's been getting better, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.09,0:41:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.97,0:41:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,She... can't move her right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.68,0:41:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.85,0:41:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,She's an artist! A manga artist!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.94,0:41:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that like losing everything?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.44,0:41:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they say that she'll be able to\N draw again when she gets better.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.48,0:41:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And what if she doesn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.49,0:41:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take away an artist's ability to draw, \Nhow are they supposed to stay in the fray?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.32,0:41:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Eriri...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.24,0:42:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,She's the greatest...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.99,0:42:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No, she's a monster capable of competing at my level!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.83,0:42:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take all that away, she might just lose herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.75,0:42:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still too early to make assumptions.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.63,0:42:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't help but worry about the worst-case situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.51,0:42:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What we should do for now is hope that she recovers.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.47,0:42:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No mater how long it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.64,0:42:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going to happen with Fields Chronicle?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.73,0:42:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you afford this kind of setback?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.31,0:42:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it. Our work is nearly done.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.23,0:42:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be finished after making a few more tweaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.90,0:42:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good. If that's the case...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.16,0:42:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying, Kasumigaoka Utaha?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.82,0:42:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We have no idea how the game is progressing as a whole.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.37,0:42:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, Sawamura-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.91,0:42:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't even know what revisions we have left!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.29,0:42:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Kousaka Akane handled everything between us and Maruzu.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.30,0:42:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.97,0:43:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Maruzu doesn't directly communicate with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.47,0:43:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to preserve the integrity of our\N work, she acted as an in-between for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.44,0:43:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,As much as I really, truly, didn't like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.23,0:43:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But now we'll actually have to face them, won't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.62,0:43:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take care of the arrangements \Nfor Akane's hospitalization and check in on her later.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.04,0:43:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you really going to have to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.12,0:43:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,She may have connections from work, but she doesn't\N have friends or the best relationship with her parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.75,0:43:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's understandable.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.30,0:43:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like Kousaka Akane wouldn't want to hear that from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.01,0:43:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the rest of you should head home.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.51,0:43:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You still have work to do, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.56,0:43:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We do, but without her direction, we're not sure how to proceed.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.02,0:43:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.69,0:43:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll talk to Maruzu about how Fields Chronicle is progressing.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.03,0:44:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Hashima-kun and I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.82,0:44:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hashima?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.74,0:44:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He has known Akane for a long time, \Nand she's trusted him with plenty in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.33,0:44:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead and update Hashima-kun with where you're at.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.92,0:44:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Glad to be working with you, Kashiwagi Eri-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.63,0:44:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the last person I wanted to work with.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.59,0:44:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows what you'll get me into.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.76,0:44:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Relax, I wouldn't dare mess with \None of Akane-san's team members.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.97,0:44:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, I'm a member of Blessing Software.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.81,0:44:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Once this is over, I'm heading back to my circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.23,0:44:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How about you head back right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.53,0:44:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need {\i1}you{\i0} for anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.91,0:44:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.82,0:44:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds like her life isn't in danger, for now at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.62,0:44:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, there's nothing left for me to do here.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.96,0:44:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I can head over there right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.92,0:44:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.63,0:45:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too late now, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.59,0:45:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, then I'll see you at the circle meeting tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.68,0:45:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Megumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.68,0:45:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,For not celebrating your birthday with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.60,0:45:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm really sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.48,0:45:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Happy birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.61,0:45:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Happy birthday, Katou-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.03,0:45:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We're a day late, but happy birthday, Megumi-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.53,0:45:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, happy birthday,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.91,0:45:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.17,0:45:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, thank you, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.67,0:45:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.88,0:45:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's grab some cake and get this meeting started.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.55,0:45:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We're still one member short, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.51,0:45:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Onii-chan is...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.47,0:45:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Something came up, so Iori won't be able\N to join our circle activities for a little while.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.73,0:45:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't really matter if he's here or not anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.40,0:45:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Megumi-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.56,0:45:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.40,0:46:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to ask him about our performance next month!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.11,0:46:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I can handle Icy Tail for—
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.24,0:46:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.24,0:46:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.53,0:46:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you really okay with that, Katou-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.16,0:46:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I might not be able to negotiate as well as him,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.20,0:46:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but I should be able to handle working with the venue or some small changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.96,0:46:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly, our circle leader here needs to \Nfocus on finishing up the game's scenario, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.55,0:46:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah, thanks. I'll leave it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.89,0:46:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.18,0:46:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll be counting on you, Katou-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.60,0:46:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Whew, that's such a relief!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.29,0:46:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for getting in the way of your circle again.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.92,0:47:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah, it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.34,0:47:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't even know what that guy was doing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.26,0:47:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He's useless when it comes to actual game development, that's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.43,0:47:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You make it sound like he's useful for anything at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.56,0:47:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, do you actually hate Hashima even more than I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.69,0:47:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, how's the work on your game coming along?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.32,0:47:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Great!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.49,0:47:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Or at least, I wish it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.78,0:47:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.45,0:47:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.87,0:47:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You're my best friend, so I won't hide anything from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.79,0:47:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, losing Kousaka Akane hurt us a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.79,0:47:41.54,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\be2\fs32\fax-0.14\c&HECECEC&\1a&H1C&\pos(1157.007,381.536)\frz311.5}Megumi
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.33,0:47:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Your deadline was coming up, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.63,0:47:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't everything nearly be done?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.09,0:47:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but we're lagging behind on reviews.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.22,0:47:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially about keeping things in line with earlier entries.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.09,0:47:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm no art director, just an artist, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.56,0:48:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you think it's okay, shouldn't that be enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.27,0:48:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This game...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.85,0:48:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.98,0:48:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the one game that, for myself \Nand for a bunch of people, needs to be perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.28,0:48:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,As Sawamura Eriri...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.90,0:48:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,No, as Kashiwagi Eri, I can't let the slightest mistake through.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.03,0:48:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to draw as fast as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.24,0:48:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,With this game, I have to make everyone \Nacknowledge me as the greatest illustrator.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.08,0:48:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If I don't, I'll have left the circle for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.58,0:48:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I would have left you and Tomoya behind for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.09,0:48:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Eriri...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.51,0:48:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.72,0:48:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just my own selfish goal, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.80,0:48:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not true. It's probably not just {\i1}your{\i0} goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.68,0:48:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true. Maybe Kasumigaoka Utaha feels the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.36,0:48:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I still have work to finish up.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.53,0:48:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, talk to you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.53,0:48:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.03,0:48:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a bit late, but happy birthday, Megumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.74,0:48:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go out and celebrate together once we're finished!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.54,0:48:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.88,0:49:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You're wrong, Eriri.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.34,0:49:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There's still one more person...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.97,0:49:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,2000)}Someone who's been watching you for the last 10 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.81,0:49:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that meeting with Maruzu was beyond hellish.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.02,0:49:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't just start the conversation \Nwith that kind of depressing news!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.82,0:49:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I've learned one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.36,0:49:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,A pure creative-type like Akane-san \Nshould never be left in charge of a project timeline.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.58,0:49:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't just laugh it off, explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.87,0:49:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't wanna hear it, but tell me what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.33,0:49:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The deadline Maruzu set has long since passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.92,0:49:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.09,0:49:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How did that happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.51,0:49:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Kashiwagi Eri and Kasumi Utako...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.72,0:49:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The more they were pressured, the more they grew.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.43,0:50:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Asked for retake after retake, continued getting better.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.85,0:50:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And Akane-san became obsessed with that growth.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.19,0:50:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How long did Kousaka-san say it \Nwould take to finish everything?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.03,0:50:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Another month.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.32,0:50:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That long?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.99,0:50:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But Maruzu is done waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.45,0:50:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,They're just going to scrap any \Nevents with unfinished art or scripts.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.62,0:50:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,From there, they say \Nthey'll rearrange everything to fit together.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.50,0:50:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently, they think they can make \Nsomething good enough with the material they have.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.88,0:50:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going to happen now?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.84,0:50:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... Akane-san's opinion will be ignored,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.26,0:50:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and Maruzu will continue according to \Ntheir own schedule with what they have.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.72,0:50:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Kashiwagi Eri and Kasumi Utako won't be able to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.06,0:50:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Their part in Fields Chronicle 13 ends here.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.44,0:50:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And you let that happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.61,0:50:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't Eriri and Utaha-senpai want to keep going?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.82,0:50:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you really think they'll just accept this?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.07,0:51:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe if Akane-san had handled the negotiations,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.24,0:51:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,she might have been able to do something about it with her pride and passion.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.04,0:51:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's impossible for me and Machida-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.87,0:51:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of the day, we're too sympathetic to the views of Maruzu's director.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.42,0:51:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.72,0:51:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't there anything that we can do?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.43,0:51:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We've done all we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.55,0:51:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.47,0:51:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen up, Tomoya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.18,0:51:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Blessing Software is your home.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.52,0:51:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You've managed to come this far with \Nthe help of your fellow circle members.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.23,0:51:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That desire of yours to do something?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.27,0:51:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You should be using that to work with Izumi, Hyoudou-san, and Katou-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.08,0:51:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Say what?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.17,0:51:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just telling you what Machida-san told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.76,0:51:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.22,0:52:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I still have over ten pieces left unfinished!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.14,0:52:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Nearly half of them need to be redrawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.39,0:52:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've only really finished the main story.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.60,0:52:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There are plenty of side stories left to be written.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.94,0:52:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This is why I didn't want to leave things to Hashima.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.23,0:52:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he probably saw this as a win.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.28,0:52:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that our work here is done, \Nwe'll be paid as outlined in our contracts,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.87,0:52:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and won't be penalized for missing the deadline.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.83,0:52:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In some ways, this is indeed a win.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.37,0:52:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you really think of this as a win?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.63,0:52:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.05,0:52:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Maruzu decided that they don't need us anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.26,0:52:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they would listen to Kousaka Akane, but \Nlistening to the complaints of a couple newbies
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.30,0:52:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,would just get in the way of finishing their biggest game, Fields Chronicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.98,0:52:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.44,0:52:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we get Maruzu to listen to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.02,0:53:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we make them let us\N work on this until we're satisfied?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.74,0:53:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Sawamura-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.99,0:53:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.16,0:53:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If we just head to Osaka ourselves to negotiate—
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.49,0:53:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.08,0:53:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If we went over there, with our high \Npride and terrible communication skills,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.12,0:53:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we'd just end up in a huge argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.25,0:53:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, isn't there someone who could negotiate for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.72,0:53:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.30,0:53:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe someone who truly believes in our skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.80,0:53:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone who believes if we were allowed to see this to completion,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.52,0:53:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that we would create a masterpiece.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.98,0:53:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone willing to kneel, cry or do anything to fight for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.07,0:53:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.40,0:53:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There is one.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.74,0:53:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.14,0:54:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.77,0:54:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah, I was still awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.10,0:54:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.19,0:54:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.77,0:54:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.04,0:54:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you're not coming to school?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.87,0:54:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.88,0:54:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to Osaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.80,0:54:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.42,0:54:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to make a game with Eriri and Kasumigaoka-senpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.47,0:54:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If I don't go, Fields Chronicle 13 will just be a good game.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.14,0:55:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that good enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.98,0:55:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It should be a masterpiece.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.78,0:55:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The legendary game that those two are capable of making.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.24,0:55:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do this, will the game end up being legendary?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.53,0:55:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.20,0:55:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, Eriri and Utaha-senpai said that they needed my help.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.00,0:55:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, is this what you want to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.05,0:55:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you have to throw away {\i1}our{\i} game?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.14,0:55:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You said it yourself, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.72,0:55:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That you'd work hard to make a legendary game.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.64,0:55:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.81,0:55:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You said we'd make it together, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.11,0:55:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But Fields Chronicle 13 is Eriri and Utaha-senpai's biggest chance in the spotlight yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.87,0:55:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But our game is {\i1}our{\i} chance, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.83,0:56:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,For the last year, we've put in everything, \Nand finally reached the spotlight, haven't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.96,0:56:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, Tomoya-kun, how should I react to this?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.01,0:56:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a 3D girl, causing you trouble, getting angry, and crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.77,0:56:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Or the 2D main heroine, sending you off, smiling and waving?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.57,0:56:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.57,0:56:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.41,0:56:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No, this is all my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.91,0:56:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.96,0:56:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Megumi...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.08,0:56:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Tomoya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.92,0:56:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.09,0:56:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't be your main heroine after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.98,0:57:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen up, Taki-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.44,0:57:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't just run in hoping to convince a company like Maruzu with passion alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.65,0:57:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Akane could use her status as a shield, but \Nyou'll have to approach the problem head-on.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.99,0:57:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll need to think of the best solution for both parties,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.99,0:57:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,be able to explain the benefits of your proposal,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.24,0:57:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and be prepared to make compromises.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.04,0:57:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And if that doesn't work?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.29,0:57:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it all comes down to passion.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.92,0:57:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether it's making hollow threats, shouting, or begging them in tears,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.88,0:57:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll have to do everything in \Nyour power to change their minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.34,0:57:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you said passion wouldn't work?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.80,0:57:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't be able to convince them with passion alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.18,0:57:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But without passion, people won't feel motivated to act.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.43,0:57:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Motivated...?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.48,0:57:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why maybe you could convince them in my place.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.56,0:57:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,With your crazy dedication for Shii-chan and Kashiwagi Eri-sensei,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.65,0:57:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,if anyone can do this, it's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.71,0:58:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.71,0:58:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back, Rinri-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.34,0:58:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Eriri, Utaha-senpai...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.59,0:58:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.55,0:58:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.43,0:58:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I got the deadline extended by another two weeks!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.39,0:58:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Why just two weeks?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.69,0:58:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You were supposed to get us a month!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.44,0:58:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you trying to kill us, Rinri-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.57,0:58:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this what I get for putting all that effort into negotiating?!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.07,0:58:37.82,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\shad1\fnAver\fs36\be1\3c&H9E703A&\c&HFFFFFF&\pos(574,693.6)}Uranus
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.07,0:58:37.82,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\shad1\fnAver\fs36\be1\3c&H9E703A&\pos(658.4,965.6)\c&HFFFFFF&}That is why I will show it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.07,0:58:37.82,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\shad1\fnAver\fs36\be1\3c&H9E703A&\pos(786,1003.2)}The true form of Venus and the truth of this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.62,0:58:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Yes! Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.45,0:58:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what I'm talking about!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.99,0:58:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The party's facing their greatest threat yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.70,0:58:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,At the brink of despair, their former arch-rival Guiel appears, saying
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.58,0:58:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'm the only one allowed to defeat you!"
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.67,0:58:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What a classic situation!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.59,0:58:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And Guiel's art here! Gosh!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.05,0:58:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,At first glance it looks plain, but it's anything but!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.09,0:58:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What the heck?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.15,0:58:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never seen such a mind-blowing expression!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.60,0:59:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything has been great so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.56,0:59:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But now we're going to make it legendary.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.77,0:59:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Remove characters?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.15,0:59:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. We're going to have to remove Lute and Sarashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.11,0:59:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This was the best compromise I could reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.99,0:59:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What? We have to cut out two characters?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.49,0:59:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They originally wanted us to cut five.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.70,0:59:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I managed to get them to agree to two.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.95,0:59:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Five?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.25,0:59:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way the story would work after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.79,0:59:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.09,0:59:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,These two are the least relevant to the main story.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.80,0:59:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So I used them as bargaining chips.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.76,0:59:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But I've already created the characters, and I like the designs...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.72,0:59:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Their stories have been written, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.52,0:59:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure we'll be able to use those down the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.10,0:59:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's keep them around in preparation for a remake.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.14,0:59:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,People will get new content and we'll double-dip on the earnings.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.73,0:59:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds so scummy.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.78,1:00:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hashima's definitely rubbed off on you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.66,1:00:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In exchange for cutting those two, \NMaruzu agreed not to make any cuts to the main story.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.33,1:00:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If anything, we'll be adding more to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.92,1:00:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This here is another scene Kousaka-san was planning.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.30,1:00:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Before I came by yesterday, \NI talked to her and compiled all the details.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.80,1:00:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You talked to Kousaka Akane?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.55,1:00:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,She's hard to deal with already.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.22,1:00:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't imagine what she's like, stuck in a hospital bed.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.39,1:00:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It was fine!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.56,1:00:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I had Machida-san there with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.56,1:00:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Wrong!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.68,1:00:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Are you even listening?!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.19,1:00:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you've finished up the content Maruzu asked for,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.36,1:00:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you're free to work on whatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.48,1:00:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be able to work towards \Nthe Fields Chronicle 13 that you and Akane-san imagined.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.57,1:00:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get started.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.95,1:00:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll show them.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.04,1:00:59.55,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnHelvetica Neue\fs44\be3\fax-0.05\frz331.6\c&H181819&\3c&H93FBBC&\pos(1045.624,236.067)}Sorry, I'm gonna be
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.04,1:00:59.55,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnHelvetica Neue\fs44\be3\fax-0.05\frz331.6\c&H181819&\3c&H93FBBC&\pos(963.787,260.429)}skipping school for a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.04,1:00:59.55,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnHelvetica Neue\fs44\be3\fax-0.05\c&H181819&\3c&H8CF3B6&\pos(1280.853,630.829)\frz333.5}Also,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.04,1:00:59.55,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnHelvetica Neue\fs44\be3\c&H181819&\3c&H8CF3B6&\frz330.8\pos(717.121,534.961)}I'm sorry about earlier.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.04,1:00:59.55,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnHelvetica Neue\be3\fs44\fax-0.05\c&H181819&\3c&H8CECAF&\pos(522.183,672.928)\frz329.4}There's a lot we need to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.04,1:00:59.55,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnHelvetica Neue\be3\fs44\fax-0.05\c&H181819&\3c&H8CECAF&\pos(489.25,723.062)\frz329.1}Lemme know if you're up for a call.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.04,1:00:59.55,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnHelvetica Neue\fs49\be4\fax-0.05\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H8CECAF&\frz332.1\pos(1190.65,160.395)}Megumi
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.80,1:01:03.30,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fs80\bord50\c&H3B3A3D&\3c&HFCFCFC&\pos(932,608)}Tomoya      4 Unread Messages
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.06,1:01:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,'Sup?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.81,1:01:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What's is it, Hyoudou-san?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.69,1:01:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I just finished writing a new song \Nand really wanted you to listen to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.82,1:01:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I just finished drawing some great art, too!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.45,1:01:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I already told you, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.99,1:01:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The circle is on break for a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.33,1:01:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know, there's not a lot of time left for Winter Comiket.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.04,1:01:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly! We're in the home stretch now, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.13,1:01:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Not my problem. Tell that to our leader.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.05,1:01:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard from Tomo. He said he'd be unable\N to participate for the next two weeks or so.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.43,1:01:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.26,1:01:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, just because Tomoya-senpai isn't here,\N doesn't mean {\i1}we{\i} need to stop working!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.43,1:01:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true. You two can go ahead and keep working.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.86,1:02:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, but...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.52,1:02:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We should be working as a team to focus our efforts!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.95,1:02:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not happening.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.53,1:02:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Without our leader around, we can't make any decisions.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.21,1:02:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.62,1:02:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We still have a leader to rely on, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.38,1:02:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.17,1:02:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.13,1:02:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We have Hashima-chan's brother here, the greatest producer around.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.14,1:02:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would you joke about that {\i1}now{\i} of all times?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.89,1:02:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I thought things would get too awkward if we stayed all serious.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.85,1:02:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, but did you {\i1}have{\i0} to make the worst joke possible?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.73,1:02:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We meant you, Megumi-san!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.32,1:02:45.57,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs80\pos(969.6,551.2)\be1\c&H172633&\3c&H15222F&}Hashima
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.58,1:03:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That was great! All of your songs are so legendary!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.34,1:03:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep the compliments coming!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.88,1:03:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But really, I'm just motivated by your art.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.22,1:03:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that sounded good.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.22,1:03:11.72,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs66\fax-0.3\be3\c&HECECEC&\1a&H1C&\frz307.3\pos(1013.143,524.857)}Onii-chan
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.89,1:03:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Play that when the protagonist and Meguri start going out.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.35,1:03:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That scene needs to be plenty emotional.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.18,1:03:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright! I got the director's approval!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.35,1:03:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The game's climax is really coming together!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.15,1:03:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we just need the script.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.90,1:03:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You promised you wouldn't bring that up, Onii-chan.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.74,1:03:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, why aren't you down here, Hashima?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.33,1:03:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You're upstairs, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.04,1:03:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.91,1:03:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I can get my work done without seeing you all face-to-face.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.04,1:03:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it a pain being off on your own?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.13,1:03:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It'd just be awkward for all of you \Nto have a guy around, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.71,1:03:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomo doesn't mind that at all, though.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.72,1:03:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't really mind either, do we?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.35,1:03:59.44,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs66\fax-0.3\be3\c&HECECEC&\1a&H1C&\frz307.3\pos(1013.143,524.857)}Onii-chan
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.64,1:03:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, letting the creative types concentrate\N and do their own thing is more my style.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.81,1:04:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hashima... You're actually a pretty decent guy, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.36,1:04:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,How many times do I have to tell you not to think of me as a nice guy?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.32,1:04:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I don't really get it. That weird concern of yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.16,1:04:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We've lived together for 15 years, and I still don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.06,1:04:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This is pretty disgusting, even for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.69,1:04:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.36,1:04:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Could I...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.73,1:04:50.78,Signs,,0,0,0,,{{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs65\be1\c&H504F55&\pos(127.4,452.6)}Megumi
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.78,1:04:51.24,Signs,,0,0,0,,{{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs65\be1\c&H504F55&\pos(127.4,452.6)}Meguri
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.95,1:04:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one painful script to read.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.58,1:04:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what is this?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.29,1:05:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,A threat from a stalker? Or some narcissistic rambling?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.25,1:05:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, it is so embarrassing \NI'd been better off not reading it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.71,1:05:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.63,1:05:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you writing that for your own game?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.55,1:05:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.72,1:05:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.09,1:05:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's part of the main heroine Meguri's route.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.97,1:05:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Well, Eriri is sleeping and all,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.60,1:05:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so I've got some free time, and...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.10,1:05:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not really a problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.23,1:05:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, this is your true responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.28,1:05:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it really that disgusting?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.61,1:05:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It sure is.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.49,1:05:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Kousaka-san complimented it, though.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.70,1:05:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,She said this was my strength. \NSomething you'd never be able to write.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.70,1:05:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Really...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.33,1:05:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like I'm reading some filthy otaku's diary.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.87,1:05:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.04,1:05:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean a filthy otaku's delusions, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.96,1:05:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.96,1:05:52.67,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs88\c&H565559&\pos(684.057,814.933)\3c&H4E2E41&}...Sorry, Megumi.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.26,1:06:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You're so persistent.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.01,1:06:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Megumi-san?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.73,1:06:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We're netting again today, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.31,1:06:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course we are.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.77,1:06:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Our schedule's been pushed to its limits.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.11,1:06:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,At this rate, we might not make it in time for Winter Comiket.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.36,1:06:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're going to help us out, Megumi-san?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.95,1:06:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to help.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.37,1:06:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just going to do my job.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.12,1:06:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to be considered a failure just because of our leader.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.08,1:06:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll show that guy we can continue without him.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.30,1:06:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the spirit, Megumi-san!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.18,1:06:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to complain about Tomoya-senpai, I'm all ears!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.01,1:06:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not just complaining, this is justified anger.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.82,1:07:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What's up?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.33,1:07:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing. Just taking a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.41,1:07:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already this late, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.17,1:07:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, have you made any progress?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.67,1:07:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a look.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.09,1:07:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.88,1:07:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You did this in just two days?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.80,1:07:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.35,1:07:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You've seen me finish seven pieces in a day before, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.35,1:07:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, you collapsed right after.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.69,1:07:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But really, this is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.81,1:07:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what got into me.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.23,1:07:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.86,1:07:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You're just improving, obviously.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.86,1:07:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what I meant.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.24,1:07:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, then what did you mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.95,1:07:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why was I able to draw at all?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.00,1:07:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Eriri?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.16,1:07:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though you're right here...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.17,1:07:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though you're watching...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.34,1:07:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Why am I still able to draw?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.13,1:07:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.67,1:07:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It'd be a problem if you couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.72,1:08:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's exactly why I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.18,1:08:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.51,1:08:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Tomoya... Once we've finished this game...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.77,1:08:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It'd be nice if we could make something together again.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.27,1:08:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.48,1:08:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do this again sometime.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.36,1:08:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.32,1:08:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how long it takes,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.24,1:08:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll keep putting in the effort,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.03,1:08:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and one day, I'll make you an offer.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.87,1:08:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.45,1:08:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be waiting. As long as it takes.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.04,1:08:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll definitely become an artist at your company!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.46,1:08:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you, it's not like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.09,1:08:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I'm angry is because he's acting \Nso irresponsible despite being our leader.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.85,1:08:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.31,1:08:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The way I see it, you're angry \Nbecause Tomo threw you to the side,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.31,1:08:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and is now hanging out with Sawamura-chan and Senpai.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.90,1:08:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just because you've got some weird misunderstanding of things.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.16,1:09:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly, weren't we supposed to be \Ndiscussing how Meguri feels about the protagonist?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.00,1:09:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,How did that turn into a discussion about me and our circle leader?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.92,1:09:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're hiding things, of course!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.09,1:09:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.76,1:09:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard from Senpai.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.84,1:09:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You two are secretly going out behind our backs, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.84,1:09:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Really?!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.55,1:09:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.39,1:09:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Kasumigaoka-senpai spread some dumb rumor.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.44,1:09:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,She says you two sneak off and call each other
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.11,1:09:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and send each other romantic messages.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.44,1:09:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't. I've been ignoring everything from him recently.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.82,1:09:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because you two got into an argument.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.20,1:09:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Are the two of you really aren't dating?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.16,1:09:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.62,1:09:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomoya-kun and I are—
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.54,1:09:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomoya-kun?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.83,1:09:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,See? I knew it!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.04,1:09:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Since when do you call Tomo by his first name?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.92,1:09:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa. It's a whole new side of Megumi-san!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.84,1:10:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.38,1:10:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The two of you have called him by his first \Nname or a nickname forever, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.47,1:10:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Jealous much?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.47,1:10:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.22,1:10:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You just keep assuming we're like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.85,1:10:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Cut it out already.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.40,1:10:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You're doing good, Izumi.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.94,1:10:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure you catch Katou-san's expressions here.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.11,1:10:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If we keep this up, we'll be able to create the best...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.41,1:10:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, the most annoying main heroine!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.04,1:10:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.87,1:10:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I get why you're so anxious, though.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.12,1:10:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to get anxious about, not for a guy like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.09,1:10:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Sawamura-chan and Senpai, could feel \Nthe pull of fate from the moment they met Tomo.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.22,1:10:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And even I've been with him since we were born.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.26,1:10:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Compared to any of us,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.60,1:10:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you and Tomo haven't had much drama.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.23,1:10:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... Am I not important enough?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.19,1:11:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Kasumigaoka-senpai tell you that, too?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.19,1:11:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If she did?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.36,1:11:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you just leave me alone?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.24,1:11:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,However I feel about Tomoya-kun\N is none of Kasumigaoka-senpai's business.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.29,1:11:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Are the two of us really not important enough?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.67,1:11:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't lump me in with you, Hashima-chan!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.08,1:11:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But, I mean...!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.42,1:11:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe to all of you, Tomoya-kun is a really special person.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.51,1:11:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But to me, he's nothing special at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.76,1:11:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He's totally normal...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.10,1:11:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.36,1:11:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the last one.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.27,1:11:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.48,1:11:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Great.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.40,1:11:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's perfect. Maruzu won't have \Na single reason to complain about.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.74,1:11:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,More like, I wouldn't let them.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.12,1:11:57.33,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs24\be1\c&H000000&\1a&H78&\pos(513.904,442.476)}Send
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.12,1:12:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We're done!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.42,1:12:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.21,1:12:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Two weeks late, though.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.09,1:12:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,More like, two weeks early!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.96,1:12:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,All thanks to a certain newbie replacement director.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.47,1:12:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.39,1:12:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the ultimate Fields Chronicle!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.27,1:12:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't deny that.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.60,1:12:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We had to work twice as hard at the end, though.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.36,1:12:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do we do now?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.40,1:12:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanna grab dinner and celebrate?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.94,1:12:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a break. I don't even feel like moving.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.54,1:12:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna head home.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.50,1:12:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,At least come and celebrate with us.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.21,1:12:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just outside help.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.59,1:12:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The two weeks I put in can't compare to \Nthe months Kousaka-san worked on this.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.13,1:12:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't my work.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.64,1:13:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But Blessing Software's new game is without a doubt mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.44,1:13:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The two weeks I've been away can't \Ncompare to the months I worked on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.15,1:13:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.44,1:13:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you feel that way, Megumi and the others might disagree.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.70,1:13:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they've gone and removed you from the credits.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.12,1:13:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got to get back to make sure that doesn't happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.58,1:13:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I really enjoyed this.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.75,1:13:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll never forget these last two weeks.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.09,1:13:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In a few hours, your own game's hell \Nwill have you forgetting all about this.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.59,1:13:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You can save these comments for the next time\N you keep us working like this for a whole year.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.22,1:13:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.22,1:13:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.06,1:13:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And he's gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.65,1:13:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Back to the circle. To Katou-san's side.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.69,1:13:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He just went back to where came from.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.48,1:13:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He never really belonged here.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.82,1:13:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That lazy otaku, who for so long put in no effort,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.62,1:14:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and had nothing but big dreams,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.87,1:14:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,got involved with Fields Chronicle...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.62,1:14:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unbelievable, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.33,1:14:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, as we agreed,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.25,1:14:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,now it's our turn to do something for him.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.59,1:14:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.92,1:14:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll have to give it our all to make sure that \Nthe main heroine's route doesn't end early.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.68,1:14:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There is one.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.18,1:14:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The only one.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.60,1:14:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone who believes in our skills...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.85,1:14:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone who would be willing to kneel, cry, or do anything—
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.98,1:14:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough, Sawamura-san.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.65,1:14:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Relying on Rinri-kun would be against the rules.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.53,1:14:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.49,1:14:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We betrayed him. We betrayed the circle.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.91,1:14:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But he forgave us. Tomoya said he'd be rooting for us!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.45,1:14:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But right now, he is...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.16,1:14:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,His circle is... making their own new work.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.63,1:14:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're putting in no less effort than we are.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.21,1:14:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If we made Rinri-kun do this for us,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.51,1:15:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we might end up crushing his dream.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.47,1:15:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But... if we give up, the promise we made to him...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.10,1:15:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Our vows to become extraordinary creators will be broken!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.28,1:15:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to rely on him no matter what,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.86,1:15:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,then there are things we need to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.12,1:15:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Like what?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.53,1:15:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The first isn't so hard.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.16,1:15:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Once our game is finished, we have to help Rinri-kun...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.42,1:15:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Help Blessing Software to finish their game.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.46,1:15:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's all...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.09,1:15:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But we did leave them before.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.13,1:15:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Would they be willing to accept our help?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.18,1:15:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That probably won't be too difficult.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.47,1:15:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,At least compared to the next thing that we'll need to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.56,1:15:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Would we need to help with something else?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.10,1:15:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not something we'd have to do any actual work for.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.44,1:15:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We just need to prepare ourselves for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.94,1:15:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Once our game is finished,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.03,1:16:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll have to support Rinri-kun's love.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.21,1:16:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.63,1:16:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You get it, don't you, Sawamura-san?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.71,1:16:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If you bring Rinri-kun into this, he won't \Nbe returning to the childhood friend route.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.30,1:16:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Or the senpai route.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.89,1:16:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, that choice will put him on the main heroine's route.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.06,1:16:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll form an even stronger bond with Katou-san and enter the climax event.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.44,1:16:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.07,1:16:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Megumi... She wouldn't...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.86,1:16:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll just have to ask her yourself then.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.37,1:16:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you still believe that an ordinary girl like her would\N never fall in love with an eccentric guy like Rinri-kun?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.75,1:16:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.67,1:16:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if we push him down that route, we'll still be friends with each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.17,1:17:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But we won't be able to pursue his dream \Nalongside him, or fill the role of his sole companion.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.78,1:17:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Kasumigaoka Utaha.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.49,1:17:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I put you in a difficult position.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.20,1:17:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems like I only ever lose. I wonder why.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.42,1:17:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You might seem like a gloomy girl with a terrible \Npersonality who schemes behind the scenes,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.55,1:17:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're actually pretty reliable, \Nand really a kind person, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.89,1:17:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, we'll get started tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.93,1:17:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Helping Rinri-kun and Katou-san make up.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.02,1:18:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we won't even need to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.57,1:18:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Megumi is more resilient than she looks.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.70,1:18:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the only one who never noticed it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.95,1:18:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That deep down, she's a dark, greedy, \Ntroublesome, and an unpleasant girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.33,1:18:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming from you, it sounds pretty convincing.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.92,1:18:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,She would never give up on Rinri-kun.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.84,1:18:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,No, she'd rather bottle up her feelings and let them smolder.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.89,1:18:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,She's the overly-sensitive type who will only be satisfied when {\i1}he{\i0} confesses.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.14,1:18:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So mean!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.15,1:18:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Megumi? What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.49,1:18:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You sent me some weird stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.49,1:18:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,An hour ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.82,1:18:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Weird stuff?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.78,1:18:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So, is it finished?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.16,1:18:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I finished both.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.08,1:18:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Fields Chronicle and the Kanou Meguri scenario.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.08,1:18:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is {\i1}really{\i0} disgusting, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.96,1:19:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I wrote how I feel about you as plainly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.92,1:19:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think there's a single girl who would be \Nhappy to receive such a disgusting love letter?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.01,1:19:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I don't really understand these things.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.02,1:19:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But, well, I guess not...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.31,1:19:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But at the very least, I'm confident that this is \Nthe story that got my heart pounding the most.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.86,1:19:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going home.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.82,1:19:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Wa-Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.24,1:19:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have any idea how behind schedule we are because of you?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.91,1:19:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.92,1:19:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I finished the scenario at least!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.04,1:19:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you think I'd let you off with just that?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.76,1:19:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But you came over here to see me!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.17,1:19:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just because I wouldn't be satisfied without complaining to you in person!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.68,1:19:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You cried for me!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.89,1:19:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Back at the train station, I know you were crying!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.77,1:20:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just because I was angry about\N you following your selfish whims!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.27,1:20:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't gone back to calling me "Aki-kun."
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.53,1:20:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,After getting this angry at someone,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.45,1:20:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't just act like I don't know them!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.46,1:20:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.92,1:20:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care, Tomoya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.05,1:20:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care about any of this.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.64,1:20:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to forgive you, but just I don't care anymore!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.27,1:20:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Because... I...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.36,1:20:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.94,1:20:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I love you, Megumi.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.61,1:20:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I love Kanou Meguri,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.94,1:20:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I love the 2D main heroine,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.11,1:20:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,but I love you, the real Katou Megumi, the most.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.21,1:21:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Why me?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.50,1:21:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not any of them?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.76,1:21:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're the only girl, \Nwith who I can be honest about my feelings.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.72,1:21:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need to pretend or act stubborn.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.39,1:21:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not because I admire you, or because of some obsession.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.98,1:21:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the main heroine anyone would envy,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.94,1:21:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but you weren't really that far out of my league.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.36,1:21:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought maybe this could work out.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.03,1:21:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think any girl would be convinced after hearing that?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.08,1:21:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess not...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.29,1:21:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Normally, you'd be right.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.17,1:21:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.63,1:21:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.05,1:21:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You managed to convince me.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.43,1:21:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe to all of you, Tomoya-kun is a really special person.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.39,1:22:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But to me, he's nothing special at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.02,1:22:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He's just an ordinary guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.77,1:22:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.86,1:22:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought he could be the one.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.32,1:22:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You might not be able to accept that.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.78,1:22:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You might dislike me for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.66,1:22:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.87,1:22:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.83,1:22:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomoya-kun... is mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.09,1:22:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Me-Megu...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.42,1:22:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Megumi...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.63,1:22:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I really am easy, aren't I?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.18,1:22:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,U-Uh... Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.05,1:22:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you love me, why did you go to back to Eriri?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.06,1:22:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.65,1:22:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you go back to Kasumigaoka-senpai?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.65,1:22:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.32,1:23:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I can't imagine you not being obsessed with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.95,1:23:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.79,1:23:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.36,1:23:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,S-Sorry! I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.70,1:23:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.45,1:23:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I got the wrong idea...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.70,1:23:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.79,1:23:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I figured since you closed your eyes, you were okay with it...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.21,1:23:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomoya-kun...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.38,1:23:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.88,1:23:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I shouldn't have done something like that out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.46,1:23:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I really can't read the—
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.18,1:24:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You weren't wrong, Tomoya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.18,1:24:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Your timing was off, is all.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.48,1:24:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Aside from that, you've got it all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.28,1:24:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's exactly what I wanted.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.91,1:24:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, then on the count of three.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.49,1:24:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.83,1:24:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,One, two, three...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.10,1:24:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They're letting you out next week, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.81,1:24:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I can move my right hand a decent amount now.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.56,1:24:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And it looks like your left hand has evolved.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.31,1:24:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,When my right hand's fully recovered, \NI'll be able to get twice as much work done!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.94,1:25:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If you try that, something even worse\N might happen, so please don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.24,1:25:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried out the beta.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.87,1:25:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.91,1:25:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.58,1:25:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.20,1:25:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Only 70% of what I wanted, made it in.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.87,1:25:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the best result we could hope for without you there.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.67,1:25:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, without me, that's as much as\N anyone could hope to get done.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.59,1:25:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Good job.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.01,1:25:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So how's your circle doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.68,1:25:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you make it in time for Winter Comiket?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.64,1:25:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hell right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.48,1:25:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess that's partially my fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.65,1:25:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I know! Next week, I'll help you—
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.65,1:25:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Just rest for a while!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.44,1:25:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you'd totally upset \Nthe circle's power balance, so please don't!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.41,1:25:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, I'm gonna head back to hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.38,1:25:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,See you soon, young man.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.50,1:26:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. If we meet again...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.76,1:26:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We will meet again.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.67,1:26:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to come over to this side, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.09,1:26:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to fight, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.64,1:26:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Chasing after Kashiwagi Eri and Kasumi Utako.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.47,1:26:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you really think I could do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.27,1:26:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,With how stubborn you are,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.03,1:26:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll be able to stay in the industry, at least.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.23,1:26:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Iori.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.40,1:26:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I'd want that.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.32,1:26:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If you ever feel like trying, bring your proposals to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.45,1:26:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's your work, even if it's right before a deadline, I'll take a look.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.79,1:26:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Kousaka-san...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.12,1:26:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And then,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.00,1:26:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll call it garbage until your heart breaks.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.63,1:26:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If I ever see you on the street, I am {\i1}not{\i} saying hello!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.15,1:27:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Tomoya-kun
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.57,1:27:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.53,1:27:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Meguri's line here
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.65,1:27:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this really okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.53,1:27:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it a typo?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.49,1:27:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,More like, it doesn't go well with the previous line.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.95,1:27:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we missing some dialogue?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.75,1:27:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.00,1:27:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.79,1:27:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.09,1:27:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh man, this awkward atmosphere!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.59,1:27:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This is why I said to avoid in-circle relationsh—
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.30,1:27:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Guys, if you let yourselves get distracted so easily, \Nwe'll never finish the game in time.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.94,1:27:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! We're in the home stretch.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.61,1:27:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Just the final scene and epilogue left, seven images total.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.82,1:27:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute! Isn't that more \Nthan what we had planned yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.82,1:27:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be helped. Meguri is just too cute!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.28,1:27:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to mention, the scene that you fixed up earlier was so good!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.83,1:28:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, where after screwing up their first kiss, \Nthey repeat it, and Meguri kisses the protagonist!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.67,1:28:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,After reading that, how could I not add more art for it?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.97,1:28:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if we may risk missing the deadline, I can't help it!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.18,1:28:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we really can't miss the deadline.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.81,1:28:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Izumi-chan's work is where we're cutting it closest after all, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.56,1:28:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We heard everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.73,1:28:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like it's time for our comeback.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.53,1:28:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold up. You guys have been coming here every day.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.65,1:28:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Fields Chronicle going to be okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.70,1:28:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine! We're professionals. We finished our work ages ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.54,1:28:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,At the cost of our schedule, sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.25,1:28:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see... So this is the latest line art, eh?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.29,1:28:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll color it.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.54,1:28:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! Wait! There's no room! Jeez!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.55,1:28:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you just work from your own house?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.80,1:28:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a short walk away!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.55,1:28:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.80,1:28:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We can only reach peak synergy \Nif we're discussing things face-to-face!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.35,1:29:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the lyrics for the ending theme, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.89,1:29:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be correcting these today, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.86,1:29:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine! All you do is complain every day!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.07,1:29:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just how your lyrics are. \NThe ideas are great, but the grammar is abhorrent.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.78,1:29:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about me, just help them debug or something!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.56,1:29:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.35,1:29:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Just getting some fresh air.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.27,1:29:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's winter already, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.27,1:29:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hashima Izumi was getting too heated up.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.07,1:29:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Izumi-chan is amazing, isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.32,1:29:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,She's learning from me, of course she'd be amazing.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.45,1:29:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The same way you grew by learning from Kousaka Akane?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.53,1:30:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have you know, I had my breakthrough on my own.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.08,1:30:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,At Nasu Kougen, fighting right up until the end...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.88,1:30:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.13,1:30:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you apologizing for?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.01,1:30:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It was over an year ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.30,1:30:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,For what happened back then, and after that...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.30,1:30:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And for whatever happens in the future.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.26,1:30:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.72,1:30:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry I couldn't be your rival ten years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.48,1:30:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for giving up on trying to compete\N after seeing you get so much better.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.15,1:30:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomoya!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.82,1:30:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for blaming you for how we\N got separated, and for avoiding you.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.74,1:30:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.45,1:30:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you saying all this now?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.21,1:30:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Back then, I wasn't considerate about others felt.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.96,1:30:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a terrible otaku who ended up hurting his friends.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.92,1:30:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like you're much different right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.21,1:30:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.13,1:30:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite that, for making up with that terrible otaku friend,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.85,1:31:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.68,1:31:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just as much of a terrible otaku too.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:05.64,1:31:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.40,1:31:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm getting cold, time to head back in.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.57,1:31:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, wait, hold on a second...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.65,1:31:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something I need to tell you...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.12,1:31:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You abused your position as leader of the circle, \Nand approached the main heroine, from what I hear.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.54,1:31:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You're dating Megumi, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.71,1:31:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,E-Eriri...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.67,1:31:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I actually...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.71,1:31:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I, uh...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.51,1:31:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.26,1:31:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I get it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.43,1:31:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm heading back in now.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.24,1:31:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Tomoya.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.78,1:32:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you in love with me?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.66,1:32:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten years ago, did you love me?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.67,1:32:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Who cares.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.89,1:32:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Who cares.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.60,1:32:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Who cares!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.40,1:32:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.12,1:32:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.58,1:32:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I was about to take a bath...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.83,1:32:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Megumi.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.54,1:32:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanna get in together?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.26,1:33:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Eriri.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.51,1:33:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,F-For what?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.39,1:33:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that I did something inconsiderate.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.06,1:33:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You and Tomoya-kun...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.77,1:33:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew about the feelings the two of you \Nharbored for each other for ten years.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.98,1:33:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And sure, some of those might be painful or unpleasant,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.44,1:33:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,but you two shared even more precious memories together,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.03,1:33:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and I knew that, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.28,1:33:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we really let things get complicated.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.75,1:33:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you want to hate me, I'll take it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.12,1:33:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you're angry with me for the next ten years...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.84,1:33:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Wait, Eri—
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.97,1:33:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, just how much do you love Tomoya?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:52.64,1:33:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I... Uh...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.56,1:34:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You forgave that traitor so quickly, and now you're going out?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.53,1:34:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no room for me to even help you.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.57,1:34:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Eriri...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.99,1:34:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It might sound strange coming from the\N one who asked him to betray you, though.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.58,1:34:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,About that... I'm not sure what to feel.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.38,1:34:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You and Tomoya, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.21,1:34:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought he was the type a normal girl would never fall for.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.72,1:34:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true that Tomoya-kun is far from normal.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.27,1:34:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But he's not nearly as special as you or Kasumigaoka-senpai.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.31,1:34:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're talking about our talent, right? And not personalities.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.94,1:34:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, it's exactly because neither of us could catch up to the two of you, that we were perfect together.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.08,1:34:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What the heck...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.00,1:35:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomoya-kun said it himself, \Nthat maybe someone on my level would be within his reach.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.05,1:35:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty sure that would normally be a reason\N to get angry and break up with him.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.64,1:35:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'm just not the type of an ordinary girl \Nwho can fall for an ordinary guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.48,1:35:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, what the heck...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.78,1:35:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously... what the heck?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.35,1:35:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright then.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.10,1:35:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We've paid off our debt to the circle.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.94,1:36:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's time to start our next real project.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.90,1:36:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have time to waste worrying about him.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.36,1:36:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Did that proposal went through?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.90,1:36:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a new series tied in with Fields Chronicle.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.24,1:36:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way Fantastic Bunko could turn it down.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.66,1:36:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.87,1:36:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's time for you to face forward.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.63,1:36:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep running.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.63,1:36:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't stop until he can't catch up anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.68,1:36:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be alright.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.97,1:36:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He will still follow, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.77,1:36:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, without a doubt, he loved us.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.94,1:36:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Not Kashiwagi Eri or Kasumi Utako,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.74,1:36:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,but us, for who we truly are.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.83,1:37:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why he'll always be chasing after us.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.71,1:37:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,As a fan, chasing after his beloved artist.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.05,1:37:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And as a rival, trying to catch up to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.60,1:37:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomoya...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.02,1:37:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomoya!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.85,1:37:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.85,1:37:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's wait for him, shall we?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.44,1:37:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:30.65,1:37:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's wait for him while advancing as fast as we can.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.25,1:37:51.76,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnKozuka Gothic Mikakunin\fs88\be1\c&HFBFBFB&\pos(962.99,782.133)}Winter Comiket, Day 3
Dialogue: 0,1:37:52.30,1:37:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We're so late!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.72,1:38:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you we didn't need so many pamphlets.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.02,1:38:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If the printer was working, we'd be fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.19,1:38:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it your job to deal with unexpected issues like these, as the circle leader?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.65,1:38:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll accept that criticism, just hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.15,1:38:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We finished the game on schedule,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.28,1:38:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,but still ended up in a rush, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.29,1:38:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll listen to your criticism, but please save it for later!
Dialogue: 0,1:38:24.67,1:38:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm... I don't know how I feel about that.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.04,1:38:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have time for that!
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.34,1:38:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's finally here. Our second Winter Comiket.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.51,1:38:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yup!
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.76,1:38:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This one is the real battle.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.27,1:38:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope a lot of people come by.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.69,1:38:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think 2000 copies was too many?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.15,1:38:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope the main heroine becomes popular.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:54.36,1:38:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course she'll be popular!
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.41,1:38:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, she's the girl I found.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.20,1:39:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The one who makes my heart beat faster than ever!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.80,1:39:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Tomoya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:38.26,1:40:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.72,1:40:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Was I able to become the main heroine you hoped for?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.10,1:40:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Not for all the players,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:50.85,1:40:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but just for one person.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.28,1:41:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Was I able to become your main heroine?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.01,1:44:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we just break up?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:14.43,1:44:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.31,1:44:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:18.14,1:44:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What's up?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.23,1:44:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would you say that?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.35,1:44:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, we never see each other lately.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:25.03,1:44:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I've told you before, haven't I?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.78,1:44:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been busy with work, \Neven on weekends. I don't have the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.86,1:44:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Working a sales job that's out of your comfort zone.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:35.16,1:44:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,After throwing away your dream of becoming a creator.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.04,1:44:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.75,1:44:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have the talent...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.30,1:44:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, I kept you waiting for years...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:50.26,1:44:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So I figured I was done chasing my dreams.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.51,1:44:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying it's my fault?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.35,1:45:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I ask you to do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.06,1:45:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I holding you back?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:05.69,1:45:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's not what I meant...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:07.86,1:45:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that's not it.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.99,1:45:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomoya-kun. That's just how {\i1}you{\i0} feel about yourself, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:14.32,1:45:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,W-What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:18.95,1:45:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You still can't forget that person, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.46,1:45:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going home.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.21,1:45:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Megumi!
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.47,1:45:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't chase our dreams together anymore, can we?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:50.57,1:45:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,'Sup, Tomoya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:54.28,1:45:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Iori?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:57.03,1:45:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Running away again?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:58.91,1:46:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it the debt collectors?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:01.71,1:46:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Or are you being chased by a girl?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:04.21,1:46:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I thought up this amazing proposal that would turn things around for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:11.01,1:46:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The client liked it too, \Nand we were about to sign a contract, but...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:17.14,1:46:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, your past misdeeds were revealed?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:21.85,1:46:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:24.10,1:46:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So hey, think you can sell this to someone?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:27.48,1:46:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,With this project, we'll reunite our two man\N dream team, and make the ultimate game.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:35.11,1:46:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How long are you going to keep chasing those stupid dreams?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:03.89,1:47:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Rinri-kun?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:11.07,1:47:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Rinri-kun...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:12.07,1:47:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Tomoya-kun...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.03,1:47:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Utaha-senpai...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.25,1:47:30.59,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnFOT-PopJoy Std B\fscx75\fs64\shad2.4\be1\fade(1500,0)\c&HE3ECED&\pos(476.445,273.667)}How to Raise a Boring Girlfriend
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.25,1:47:30.59,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnFOT-PopJoy Std B\fscx75\fs64\shad2.4\be1\fade(1500,0)\c&HE9F3F5&\pos(629.111,355)}The Final Chapter
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.79,1:47:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,On that night—
Dialogue: 0,1:47:28.29,1:47:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The heck are you singing?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:31.34,1:47:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:33.42,1:47:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell is this?!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:39.09,1:47:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,G-G-G-G-Gimme a break!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:39.64,1:47:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Sorry. I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:40.85,1:47:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Please excuse us.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:42.47,1:47:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this supposed to be? What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:45.60,1:47:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:47.35,1:47:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Kasumi Utako's masterpiece,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.11,1:47:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and Blessing Software's latest project.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:52.77,1:47:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The plot for How to Raise a Boring Girlfriend: The Final Chapter.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:55.78,1:48:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How could you do this in the movie? That too in the epilogue! This dumb fantasy should be illegal or something!
Dialogue: 0,1:48:01.03,1:48:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You really had me sweating there, in more ways than one.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:03.70,1:48:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm. My character was pretty trashy. I liked it.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:08.79,1:48:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I still don't understand your tastes at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:11.96,1:48:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So there you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:13.21,1:48:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The plot is finished, so we just need to get\N the art and development schedule going—
Dialogue: 0,1:48:17.42,1:48:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way we're making this. What a load of bullshit.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:20.68,1:48:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We're supposed to be making a sequel to our game.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:24.93,1:48:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You tossed the last game's happy ending right out the window!
Dialogue: 0,1:48:27.89,1:48:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This is as bad as killing off the last game's protagonist in a car accident.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:32.19,1:48:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I got so excited, I stayed up all night writing this, too...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:35.57,1:48:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It definitely reads like it was written overnight!
Dialogue: 0,1:48:38.61,1:48:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Most importantly, why is the main heroine\N this time some older, gloomy, yandere?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:43.95,1:48:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened to the wonderful, blonde childhood friend?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:46.70,1:48:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well naturally, if I were contracted to, I'd write that route too.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:50.58,1:48:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:51.58,1:48:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe for another two million yen.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:54.59,1:48:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'll take care of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:56.59,1:48:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't bribe her!
Dialogue: 0,1:48:59.59,1:49:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Utaha...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:01.47,1:49:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,This may be an offer from some no-name company, \N but you should still take it seriously.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:08.22,1:49:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not fair, Eriri.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:10.60,1:49:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I've researched this company's past works.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:14.27,1:49:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Based on that, I came up with a plot \NI thought their fans would enjoy most.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:17.53,1:49:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right. If you say so.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:20.49,1:49:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems like we'll want to discuss the direction \Nwith our employers here before starting on anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:25.87,1:49:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that was the plan from the start.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:29.33,1:49:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, they are a popular and well-established company.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:34.08,1:49:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it with that weird reaction of yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:36.38,1:49:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you the employer here?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:40.72,1:49:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but I mean...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:43.05,1:49:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just, we're finally doing this.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:47.22,1:49:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It took a little longer than I hoped, though.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:50.10,1:49:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels like we were working together just yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:53.44,1:49:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Time passed by in a flash for us.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:57.73,1:49:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,1:50:00.07,1:50:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:01.90,1:50:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you are, Rinri-kun.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:04.41,1:50:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn you!
Dialogue: 0,1:50:13.58,1:50:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:14.87,1:50:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Your meeting with Eriri and—
Dialogue: 0,1:50:17.54,1:50:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomoya-kun?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:18.92,1:50:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Megumi... Megumi!
Dialogue: 0,1:50:21.26,1:50:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not gonna go anywhere, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:23.22,1:50:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't leave me, will you?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:25.51,1:50:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Did someone show you some terrible plot writing?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:28.30,1:50:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, like Kasumigaoka-senpai?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:31.02,1:50:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't just get it right!
Dialogue: 0,1:50:37.27,1:50:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's finally going to come true, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:39.52,1:50:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Our dream.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:42.03,1:50:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh man, being able hear that from you is such a relief!
Dialogue: 0,1:50:46.36,1:50:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds like she really did traumatize you.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:49.66,1:50:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, once this project kicks off, things are going to get busy!
Dialogue: 0,1:50:53.54,1:50:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been busy ever since you decided to make the game.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:00.92,1:51:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you, Director.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:04.80,1:51:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything depends on you, Scenario Writer-san.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:09.51,1:51:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure to make good use of those two, Vice President.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:12.97,1:51:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let them run over you, President.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:17.65,1:51:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's make this happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:19.06,1:51:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't make it happen, who will?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:26.49,1:51:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait until we're back home.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:30.49,1:51:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? It's open?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:33.20,1:51:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Wha—
Dialogue: 0,1:51:35.21,1:51:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh hey, welcome home.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:37.12,1:51:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome home, Tomoya-san, Megumi-san.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:40.54,1:51:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What are you two doing here?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:43.55,1:51:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This great phrase popped into my head, \Nand I just couldn't sit still.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:49.89,1:51:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Same for me!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:50.64,1:51:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought of a really good character design, so I couldn't just sit around!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:53.97,1:51:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The office is next door!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:55.93,1:51:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And you two aren't even working!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:58.06,1:52:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but we used to work \Nin your room all the time, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:02.48,1:52:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not just a circle anymore, we're a company!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:04.73,1:52:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mix work with your personal lives!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:06.11,1:52:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mix work with our personal lives?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:07.86,1:52:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Are {\i1}you{\i} seriously telling us that?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:10.32,1:52:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I mean...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:11.37,1:52:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:12.49,1:52:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Who do you think you are?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:13.79,1:52:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's rich coming from you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:16.00,1:52:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I really just hear you say that?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:18.92,1:52:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,These dishes and the furniture,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:20.58,1:52:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomoya definitely didn't pick out any of this.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:23.42,1:52:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Eriri...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:27.76,1:52:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I suppose you pass, barely.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.64,1:52:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this what you do when you go to \Nsomeone else's place for the first time?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:33.85,1:52:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't act so distant, Katou-chan!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:36.85,1:52:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:37.81,1:52:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Those two are going to be working with us now, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:42.40,1:52:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What a handful...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:45.65,1:52:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, those {\i1}two{\i}?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:55.91,1:52:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:57.37,1:53:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided to go ahead and take a shower first, Katou-san.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:00.79,1:53:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Kasumigaoka-senpai...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:03.00,1:53:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}How long has it been since we had the whole team together?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:06.67,1:53:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}We're going all out tonight! Let's call your brother over too!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:09.92,1:53:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Alright!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:10.72,1:53:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}I've got the food taken care of!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:15.10,1:53:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Please forgive me!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:17.27,1:53:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute, I didn't even do anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:20.52,1:53:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You're so loud, Tomoya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:22.90,1:53:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on, Megumi...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:26.15,1:53:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:27.65,1:53:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you go entertain the guests?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:30.15,1:53:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't do that...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:32.20,1:53:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,At the very least,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:35.78,1:53:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,bring this out.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:38.29,1:53:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a while, hasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:40.62,1:53:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the six of us were together.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:44.42,1:53:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:45.92,1:53:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we begin?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:48.21,1:53:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Our first overnight meeting in years.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:50.05,1:53:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:51.63,1:53:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a bit annoyed that they're intruding in on us,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:56.51,1:53:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so I'll manage with this for now.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:04.73,1:54:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They're here!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:06.36,1:54:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been waiting!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:08.02,1:54:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You really kept us waiting, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:10.07,1:54:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Were those last ten seconds really necessary?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:13.78,1:54:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on. I'm not falling for your bait.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:17.74,1:54:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be rude!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:20.29,1:54:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! Okay!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:22.04,1:54:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get this started!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:25.38,1:54:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,To the reunion of Blessing Software's original members!
